{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This approach could effectively forecast long-period ground motions of large earthquakes regarding amplitude, waveform envelope shape, spectral characteristics, and duration.",
    "Due to computational constraints and insufficient knowledge of the underground structure at short wavelengths, physics-based simulation (PBS) ground motions are reliable only in the long-period range (typically, approximately 1 s).",
    "ML has been applied to convert long-period to short-period PBS waveforms and obtain broadband ground-motion waveforms.",
    "In the approach proposed by Paolucci et al. (2018), the short-period response spectra were estimated using an ML model from the long-period ones simulated by PBS.",
    "Then, the short-period components of the original PBS waveforms were enriched using a stochastic simulation to match the estimated response spectra."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In the approach proposed by Paolucci et al. (2018), the short-period response spectra were estimated using an ML model from the long-period ones simulated by PBS."
  ]
}